TV game show Celebrity Game Night is coming back for a third season. Radio and TV presenter Anele Mdoda is returning as the host together with team captains, Ayanda Thabethe and Jason Goliath. The new season starts on Sunday, 13 February, at 8pm on E! (DStv Channel 124). This season’s celebrity contestants have been announced – ranging from radio and TV personalities, to comedians and musicians. “Join Anele, Ayanda and Jason as well as an array of local comedians, musicians, actors and media personalities as they’ve never been seen before. Popular guests are back to compete in a series of raucous challenges, including Minnie Dlamini-Jones, Boity Thulo, Kelly Khumalo, Donovan Goliath, Mpho Popps, Roxy Burger, Lerato Kganyago, Moonchild, Schalk Bezuidenhout, Anne Hirsch and Thembi Seete,” wrote E! in a statement. ALSO READ : MESHACK SCORES A NEW ROLE! “During the course of the 10 one-hour episodes, teams will also be bolstered by the star power of Rowlene, Sandile Mahlangu, Dineo Langa and Skhumba, among many more famous faces,” it continued. For the first time, the show will also feature guests from across the continent, including comedian Josh Alfred, presenter Stephanie Coker, as well as Nollywood power couple Ibrahim and Linda Suleiman via video link. The award-winning series is based on the prime time Emmy award-winning series Hollywood Game Night.